text.section:
A license, certification, or certificate of acceptability may be denied, suspended, or revoked on the following grounds:
A showing of insolvency in a court of competent jurisdiction;
Material misstatement in application for license, certification, or certificate of acceptability;
Willful failure to comply with any provisions of KRS 227.550 to 227.660 or any rule or regulation promulgated by the board under KRS 227.550 to 227.660;
Willfully defrauding any buyer;
Willful failure to perform any written agreement with any buyer or retailer;
Failure to have or to maintain an established place of business;
Failure to furnish or maintain the required insurance;
Making a fraudulent sale, transaction, or repossession;
Employment of fraudulent devices, methods, or practices in connection with the requirements under the statutes of this state with respect to the retaking of goods under retail installment contracts and the redemption and resale of such goods;
Failure by a retailer to put the title to a manufactured home, mobile home, or recreational vehicle in his name after said retailer has acquired ownership of the manufactured home, mobile home, or recreational vehicle by trade or otherwise;
Violation of any law relating to the sale or financing of manufactured homes, mobile homes, or recreational vehicles.
